    "In addition, efficient allocation of berths is important for terminal and port operations.",
    "Optimal berth allocation ensures smooth vessel traffic and minimizes waiting times for ships.",
    "For these problems various constraints and parameters such as vessel types, handling requirements, and berth availability are taken into account (Bierwirth and Meisel 2015).",
    "Another important aspect of managing seaport terminals is the allocation of quay cranes to handle ships, as is discussed, e.g., by Yang et al. (2023).",
